{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}} In the field of [[linguistics]], '''polygenesis''' is the view that human languages evolved as several lineages independent of one another. It is contrasted with [[Proto-Human language|monogenesis]], which is the view that human languages all go back to a single common ancestor.
Polygenesis is not to be confused with the [[wave model (linguistics)|wave theory]], originally propounded by [[Johannes Schmidt (linguist)|Johannes Schmidt]].
